// Character class `[\w\-@.]+`:
// \w  = [A-Za-z0-9_] (ASCII only by default in JS regex without u flag)
// \-  = literal -
// @, . = literals
// So an actorId like `user-α` or `привет@example.com` or `😀admin` would not be fully matched.
// Example: `entity_created by привет@example.com`
//   match: `by `, then `[\w\-@.]+` tries to consume — \w doesn't match cyrillic,
//   so match consumes ZERO chars, regex fails, NO replacement happens.
// Result: label stays `entity_created by привет@example.com` — actor identity FULLY visible.

